 Class Inheritance<body>
  Class Inheritance  
    Class Inheritance 

    A TV is a kind of home electronics appliance  And so are radio, VCR, CD player, LD player    All appliances share common properties and behavior  They can play audio, be turned on/off, etc.  They also exhibit some differences    One can construct a Home Electronics Appliance class  All appliances are derived from it  This is called inheritance    Humans are good at classifying, building taxonomies  Corresponds to OO inheritance hierarchies       
 
   

